    "body": "### Problem\n\n```bash\ncd /path/to/neovim\nnvim --headless --clean -u minimal.lua -p test/functional/plugin/lsp/*\n```\n\nminimal.lua:\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config('lua_ls', {\n  cmd = { 'lua-language-server' },\n  filetypes = { 'lua' },\n  root_markers = { '.git' },\n})\nvim.lsp.enable('lua_ls')\nvim.o.foldmethod = 'expr'\nvim.o.foldexpr = 'v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()'\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('LspAttach', {\n  callback = function(args)\n    local client = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(args.data.client_id)\n    if client:supports_method('textDocument/foldingRange') then\n      local win = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()\n      vim.wo[win][0].foldexpr = 'v:lua.vim.lsp.foldexpr()'\n    end\n  end,\n})\nvim.uv.new_timer():start(2000, 100, function()\n  vim.schedule(function()\n    pcall(vim.cmd.bd)\n  end)\nend)\n```\n\n```\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_folding_range.lua:119: assertion failed!\nstack traceback:\n               [C]: in function 'assert'\n               /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_folding_range.lua:119: in function 'multi_handler'\n               /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_folding_range.lua:140: in function 'handler'\n               /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:682: in function ''\n               vim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman -S neovim\n\ncc @ofseed ",
